---
import { Image } from 'astro:assets';
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';

import portrait from '../assets/about/portrait-graduation.webp';
import desertFilm from '../assets/about/photo-desert-film.webp';
import sfStreet from '../assets/about/photo-sf-street.webp';
import saigon from '../assets/about/photo-saigon.webp';
import coffeeDesk from '../assets/about/coffee-desk.webp';
import coffeeMachine from '../assets/about/coffee-machine.webp';

const photography = [
  { src: desertFilm, alt: 'Film photograph of an empty dirt road at dusk in the high desert, power lines running toward distant hills under a pink-blue sky' },
  { src: saigon, alt: 'A city street seen from above under heavy storm clouds, a sliver of sunset on the horizon' },
  { src: sfStreet, alt: 'Black-and-white street photograph of a San Francisco street at dusk near Union Square, parked cars and tall buildings receding into the distance' },
];
---

<Base
  title="About - Phuc Truong"
  description="Phuc Truong is a new-grad software engineer (UCLA, B.S. Mathematics of Computation) who builds full-stack web apps and runs them on his own homelab. Based in San Jose, CA."
>
  <section class="grid gap-10 md:grid-cols-[minmax(0,1fr)_18rem] md:items-start md:gap-12">
    <div>
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-semibold">About</h1>

      <div class="mt-6 max-w-measure space-y-5 text-muted">
        <p>
          I'm Phuc Truong, a new-grad software engineer. I graduated from UCLA
          in 2026 with a B.S. in Mathematics of Computation, and I'm actively
          looking for a full-stack or software engineering role.
        </p>
        <p>
          What I care about most is building things that actually run in
          production and staying responsible for them - not demos that work
          once on a laptop. Most of what I know, I learned by building something
          and then having to keep it alive. I run a <a href="/homelab"
          class="text-accent hover:underline">homelab</a> - a mini PC and a NAS
          I put together myself - and every project on this site is served from
          that hardware, over my own network. When <a href="/projects/planbear"
          class="text-accent hover:underline">PlanBear</a>'s cloud bill stopped
          making sense, I moved it home. When I wanted to understand anomaly
          detection, I pointed a model at my own server's telemetry and watched
          it over-alert. I'm a hands-on learner, and running infrastructure I'm
          actually on the hook for has taught me more than any single class.
        </p>
        <p>I'm based in San Jose, CA.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="mt-7 flex flex-wrap gap-x-5 gap-y-2 text-sm">
        <a href="/Phuc_Truong_Resume.pdf" class="text-accent hover:underline">Resume (PDF)</a>
        <a href="mailto:ptruong9090@gmail.com" class="text-accent hover:underline">ptruong9090@gmail.com</a>
        <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/ptruong9090/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-accent hover:underline">LinkedIn</a>
      </div>
    </div>

    <figure class="md:pt-1">
      <Image
        src={portrait}
        alt="Phuc Truong at UCLA graduation in front of Royce Hall at golden hour, wearing a Class of 2026 Mathematics of Computation stole"
        class="w-full rounded-lg border border-border"
        widths={[288, 576]}
        sizes="(min-width: 768px) 18rem, 100vw"
      />
      <figcaption class="mt-2 text-xs text-muted">Royce Hall, UCLA - Class of 2026.</figcaption>
    </figure>
  </section>

  <section class="mt-16 border-t border-border pt-12">
    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold">Photography</h2>
    <div class="mt-5 max-w-measure space-y-5 text-muted">
      <p>
        I shoot a Fujifilm X100V, usually with a pro-mist filter. What I like
        about it is getting the shot right in the camera - I didn't want to
        spend time editing, I wanted to see the photo straight out of the camera
        and keep it that way. Before the X100V I shot with a Sony a6400 (Tamron
        28-75, Sigma 16mm).
      </p>
      <p>
        I'm drawn to quiet, in-between scenes: an empty road at dusk, a city
        from above right before the rain, a street after the crowd thins out.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-7 gap-3 [column-count:2] md:[column-count:3]">
      {
        photography.map((p) => (
          <Image
            src={p.src}
            alt={p.alt}
            class="mb-3 w-full rounded-lg border border-border"
            widths={[300, 500]}
            sizes="(min-width: 768px) 33vw, 50vw"
          />
        ))
      }
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="mt-16 border-t border-border pt-12">
    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold">Coffee</h2>
    <div class="mt-5 max-w-measure space-y-5 text-muted">
      <p>
        I've never worked as a barista - I just love to drink coffee. I pull my
        own shots at home and enjoy tasting how different beans and roasts each
        have their own flavor profiles, always chasing the perfect cup. I
        practice latte art too.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-7 grid grid-cols-2 gap-3">
      <Image
        src={coffeeDesk}
        alt="A latte with a rosetta poured into a glass, held over a desk with a mechanical keyboard, monitors, and a laptop"
        class="w-full rounded-lg border border-border"
        widths={[400, 700]}
        sizes="(min-width: 768px) 33vw, 50vw"
      />
      <Image
        src={coffeeMachine}
        alt="A latte with leaf art in a ceramic cup next to a home espresso machine on a kitchen counter"
        class="w-full rounded-lg border border-border"
        widths={[400, 700]}
        sizes="(min-width: 768px) 33vw, 50vw"
      />
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>
